<HEADLINE> Aftershock Hits Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- An aftershock, estimated at 4.5
degrees on the open-ended Richter scale, rocked Cyprus Friday
evening, more than 48 hours after a much stronger tremor hit the
island on Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the aftershock was located in an area north of
the southern coastal town of Limassol, said Sotiris Krambis, a
senior geological official at the Cyprus Geological Survey
Department.
</P>
<P>
The tremor is believed to have been felt by people across the
country.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-five people were injured or sustained shocks in
Wednesday's earthquake which was measured at 5.8 degrees on the
Richter scale and followed by a number of aftershocks.
</P>
<P>
There were also numerous reports of damage to homes in the
Limassol district. 
</P>
</TEXT>
