<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran said it will use every possible legal means to
identify and punish those Taliban militants responsible for the
1998 killing of Iranian diplomats and reporter in northern
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
According to the official Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA)
Friday, Iranian Foreign Ministry's director for Afghan affairs,
Mohammad Ebrahim Taherian, said if the international community
fails to arrest and punish the "murderers," Iran would use
whatever legal tools available to punish them. (BC-Iran-Afghanistan)
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Warplanes of the United States and Britain have
shelled grain warehouses in the southern Iraqi province of
Muthana, the Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
INA quoted a Trade Ministry spokesman as saying that at 19:30
(1530 GMT) Tuesday, U.S. and British warplanes bombed warehouses
of the state company of construction materials which were used by
the State Grain Board.
</P>
<P>
He said that the bombardment caused damage to the rice in the
warehouses as well as the windows, ceilings and walls of some
warehouses. (BC-Iraq-Western Attacks)
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus President Glafcos Clerides has received
personal thanks from Israeli President Ezer Weizman and Prime
Minister Ehud Barak for freeing two Israelis jailed in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The two Israelis, Igar Damary, 49 and Udi Hargov, 37, were
sentenced in February to three years in jail for approaching a
restricted area and possessing banned listening devices without
the permission of the Cyprus authorities. (BC-Cyprus-Israel)
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel Friday approved a
constitutional change in the Political Parties Law, the
presidential press center said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The proposal for the amendment in the Political Parties Law was
adopted by the Parliament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the new law, a banned political party cannot be
established again under another name. (BC-Turkey-Politics)


13/08/99 19:49 GMT

NNNN
04:01 04:01 g # PAB
