<HEADLINE> Albanian Prime Minister Visits Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli
Majko arrived in Pristina early Friday on a visit to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
This is the first trip by an Albanian leader since 1912, the
Albanian Telegraphic Agency (ATA) said.
</P>
<P>
Majko visited the Pristina University after his arrival in
Kosovo, saying that the Pristina University is the cradle of the
current politicians of Kosovo and it should be the first place he
has to see.
</P>
<P>
Majko expressed his support to close cooperations between
Albanian and Pristina Universities, saying that students in
Albanian and Kosovo should learn with the same book as they speak
the same language.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian Information Agency (MIA) Friday also reported
that Majko is paying an unofficial visit to Kosovo, mainly for
family reasons, and he is expected to meet Kosovo Liberation Army
leader Hashim Tachi and Kosovo Democratic League leader Ibrahim
Rugova.  
</P>
</TEXT>
