<HEADLINE> Libya Hopes to Invest in Ethiopia: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Libya has strong desire to
make investment in Ethiopia, visiting Libyan investment delegation
leader M.A, Elhuwed said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles Zenawi,
Elhuwed, chairman and general manager of the Libyan Arab Foreign
Investment Company, said Ethiopia had great investment potentials
both in terms of human and natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Libya has designed projects in certain areas of investment and
would soon begin activities to implement them in the country, a
spokesman for the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry quoted Elhuwed as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Meles on his part told the Libyan delegation that Ethiopia
would happily welcome and encourage Libya's participation in
investment here.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, Meles and Elhuwed discussed the
existing friendly relations and bilateral cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Elhuwed and his entourage, who arrived here Wednesday, had held
talks with officials of the Ethiopian investment authority, the
Ministry of Mines and Energy, as well as exporting promotion and
privatization agencies on the investment potentials in the Horn of
Africa country.
</P>
<P>
They also exchanged views with the authorities of the Ethiopian
Chamber of Commerce and private entrepreneurs who are engaged in
foreign trade, the spokesman added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
