<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, South Korea Sign Sports Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia and South Korea
have signed a sports cooperation agreement which will enable the
two countries to exchange expertise and information, Ethiopian
News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed here Thursday, the two countries
will exchange athletes, coaches, sports teams and experts as well
as information in sports science.
</P>
<P>
Besides, South Korea will also help Ethiopia train coaches,
senior sports professions and administrators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
