<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cape Verde Diplomatic Policy to Continue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luanda, August 13 (xinhua) -- The New Foreign Minister of Cape
Verde said Friday in his inaugural ceremony that he will continue
the country's diplomatic policy delineated by his immediate
predecessor Jose Luis de Jesus.
</P>
<P>
Rui Figueiredo Soares told a press conference after the
ceremony held in Praia, capital of Cape Verde, that "I will make
effort to serve Cape Verde and the development of my country
through my work in the Foreign Ministry."
</P>
<P>
The 43-year-old foreign minister stressed that the Foreign
Ministry will go on keeping good relations with friendly countries
and hopes that his effort will promote the development of Cape
Verde, a report from Praia said.
</P>
<P>
Soares, former minister of the presidency of the Council of
Ministers, was appointed as foreign minister on Wednesday by Prime
Minister Carlos Veiga, to replace his out-going predecessor Jose
Luis de Jesus, who offered his resignation in a bid to run for the
position of a judge of the International Tribunal of Maritime
Laws. 
</P>
</TEXT>
