<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwanda to Host Int'l Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is said that nine countries from Africa, Asia, America and
Europe have registered to participate in Kigali international
Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
According to Paul Rusagara, the Director of General of Services
in the CCIR, the participating countries include Uganda, Kenya,
Zambia, Burundi, Egypt, Iran, Switzerland and the United States of
America.
</P>
<P>
"Rwanda, the host, will be represented by 150 business people
and enterprises, among whom industrialists, entrepreneurs and
Artists," the sources at CCIR said.
</P>
<P>
The Trade Fair stands will be hired at 10 to 25 U.S. dollars
for the respective local business people, while for the foreigners
each will be rented for about 350 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
This international exhibition will encourage bilateral
cooperation between Rwanda and the participating countries . It
will also assist in advertizing Rwanda's industrial products at
the global market, the CCIR officials indicated.
</P>
<P>
The 1999 Rwanda Trade Fair comes just one month after the
first Egyptian Trade Fair hosted by Rwanda had attracted crowds
which expressed special interests in Egyptian products.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the CCIR has called on the Rwandan government
to construct a permanent trade fair ground. 
</P>
</TEXT>
