<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin held talks with visiting
Tajikistan President Emomali Rakhmonov in Dalian, a northeastern
port city.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of state exchanged views on bilateral ties and
issue of common concern.
</P>
<P>
President Rakhmonov arrived in this scenic coastal city, the
third leg of his four-day goodwill visit to China, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
China Rejects Nicaragua Proposal on Taiwan's Status
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao today expressed
strong condemnation of and firm opposition to a proposal by
Nicaragua and some other countries calling for discussions of
Taiwan's "representation" in the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out: "This is a wilful trample on the purpose and
principles of the U.N. Charter and gross interference in China's
internal affairs, and we strongly condemn and firmly oppose this."
</P>
<P>
China, Tajikistan Sign Four Documents
</P>
<P>
China and Tajikistan signed four documents this evening
following talks between Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
Tajikistan President Emomali Rakhmonov.
</P>
