<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High Death Toll in Rebel Attack Denied by Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Burundi government has
rejected media reports that over 475 civilians were killed in
renewed clashes with Hutu rebels in the suburbs south of capital
Bujumbura early this week, saying just a dozen were killed, the
Rwanda News Agency (RNA) reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The attack in broad day-light on a market place at Kanyosha
had caused panic among residents who fled to the capital, while
the army was engaged in mop-up operations of the Hutu rebels in
the hills of Mubimbi, Mutambu, and Muhuta communes.
</P>
<P>
The army and the Hutu rebels have been trading accusations,
blaming each other for the atrocities committed against civilians.
</P>
<P>
''This is mere fabrication. I do not know where those reports
got the figures,'' Appollinaire Gahungu, presidential spokesman
told RNA in a phone interview from capital Bujumbura. Gahungu said
that only 11 assailants and one gendarme were killed during the
fighting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
