<DOCNO> XIE19990814.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwanda, OPEC Agree to Resume Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The agreement was reached during discussions between OPEC
president Rilwa Lukman and top Rwandan government officials, when
Lukman concluded a two-day visit to Rwanda Thursday, the Rwanda
News Agency (RNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Lukman said that OPEC will release about over 18 million U.S.
dollars donated by the organization before the 1994 war and
genocide. The amount will be used to import petroleum products.
</P>
<P>
''Before 1994, OPEC had given Rwanda financial support to
implement different projects, including the construction of
roads,'' Lukman declared. ''The same relations were extended to
other fields like communication, transport, agriculture, and
health,'' he added.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the OPEC president and Rwandan authorities
devised ways of resuming bilateral ties. 
</P>
