<HEADLINE> U.S. Offers New Aid to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The United States will
provide Ethiopia with new contributions totalling over 12 million
U.S. dollars to support emergency food relief efforts currently
underway in Ethiopia, the U. S. embassy announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The latest U.S. donation will be used to support the Ethiopian
government's efforts to save lives, improve the nutrition of
drought affected people and to support household food security
recovery, a press statement by the U.S. embassy said.
</P>
<P>
Five million people were reportedly in need of emergency food
assistance in Ethiopia this year following a long period of
drought in large parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the 14-month-old Ethio-Eritrea border conflict has
 displaced more than 330,000 people from their homes.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. government food aid to Ethiopia since October of 1998
has reached 310,000 metric tons and is valued at more than 80
million dollars, according to a press release. 
</P>
</TEXT>
