<HEADLINE> Murder Suspect for S. African Opposition Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A suspect has been arrested
 for the assassination of a South African opposition party leader
Sifiso Nkabinde, police said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a news conference in Pietermaritzburg in the east of
the country Friday, Bulelani Ngcuka, national director of Public
Prosecutions, said the suspect was arrested in KwaZulu-Natal
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The breakthrough was made by a team of investigators after six
months of hard work.
</P>
<P>
Nkabinde was gunned down in Richmond, KwaZulu-Natal, on January
23, shortly after he was elected as leader of the United
Democratic Movement (UDM) in the province.
</P>
<P>
In April last year, Nkabinde was acquitted on 16 murder charges
and two of incitement to murder. The charges pertained to several
incidents of violence in Richmond.
</P>
<P>
Ngcuka said a further three arrests were imminent and warrants
of arrest had already been issued by the Richmond magistrate.
</P>
<P>
He declined to give the exact location or any further details
of where the man was arrested, except to confirm that the suspect
was from KwaZulu- Natal.
</P>
<P>
He said three other arrests were expected to take place over
the weekend. 
</P>
