<HEADLINE> Johnson Retains IBF Bantamweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- IBF junior bantamweight
champion Mark Johnson defensed his title Friday night with a
unanimous decision as he stopped Mexican Jorge Lacierva in the
ninth in Mashantucket, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Referee Steve Smoger stopped the bout at 2:07 of the ninth
round when Lacierva was badly beaten.
</P>
<P>
Judges William Hutt and Don O'Neill scored it 79-73 in favour
of Johnsen, while Judge Clark Sammartino scored it 77-75.
</P>
<P>
Johnson has won 37 straight fights. His only loss came in his
second pro fight nine years ago against Richie Wenton in Ireland.
</P>
