</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Two rival camps in East Timor kicked off their
campaigns ahead of the August 30 U.N.-administered autonomy ballot
on Saturday, according to the Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the 14-day campaign, Governor Abilio Jose Osorio
Soares is of the view that a door-to-door campaign model is much
better than others to implement in avoiding the two rival groups
from any unexpected possibilities. (Indonesia-East Timor)
</P>
