- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Twenty-five pilgrims were killed and 15 others
injured when a bus overturned and plunged into a deep ditch last
night in Sitamarhi, Bihar, local officials said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sitamarhi District Magistrate R.N. Prasad said that the
accident occurred when the driver of the bus lost control over the
vehicle at a sharp bend.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of 25 people were recovered from the bus Saturday
morning, he added. The injured were admitted to a local hospital.
(India-Bus Accident)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Former Chilean leader Augusto Pinochet intends to
fight extradition from Britain to Spain where he suspects he would
not get a fair trial, his son said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Marco Antonio Pinochet told BBC that his 83-year-old father
would not go to Madrid voluntarily to face charges of human rights
abuses.
</P>
<P>
He said his father, who is currently under house arrest outside
London, is in poor health. He said he is worried that his father
might die in custody.( BRITAIN-PINOCHET)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
