<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990814.0066 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK to Kick-off over 30 Millennium Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is expected to
present over 30 community-building programs with the themes of
culture, recreation and health education to celebrate the new
millennium.
</P>
<P>
Jointly sponsored by the Provisional Urban Council (PUC) and
the Provisional Regional Council (Pro RC), the programs will be
staged from now through 2000.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the kick-off ceremony Saturday, Ada Wong Ying-kay,
chairman of the PUC's Working Group on Millennium Activities, said
the new Millennium celebration is designed to review the past at
this historical moment, and at the same time look into the future
in a concerted effort to build a better city in the new era.
</P>
<P>
She said the Urban Council have especially organized an
exhibition on "Urban Council - Past, Present and Future," and it
also plans to spend two years' time to compile a book depicting in
detail the historical development of the Urban Council.
</P>
<P>
"As regards cultural activities, we will have a large-scale
arts festival 'Celebration of Hong Kong Performing Arts - A
Tribute to the New Millennium'," she said.
</P>
<P>
The two Municipal Councils will also co-organize the "Good
Books of the Millennium" event with the Radio Television Hong Kong,
inviting Chinese from all over the world to choose the ten most
influential books of the Millennium.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Wing-kee, chairman of Pro RC's Working Group on
Millennium Celebration, said Mass Gymnastics towards an Era of
Health, which is suitable for all ages will be launched in
September 1999 to enhance public awareness of the importance of
health.
</P>
<P>
"'The Sports Promotion Carnival' will present the development
and changes of Hong Kong's recreational and sport activities for
the past century," he said.
</P>
<P>
Other large-scale events include International and Hong Kong
Sand Sculpture Competitions, Chinese Table-Setting Competition,
Chinese Arts Festival, and Chinese Dinosaur Fossils Exhibition.
</P>
<P>
On New Year's Eve, members of the two Municipal Councils will
plant a Millennium time capsule, which will be unearthed in 2020.
</P>
<P>
At midnight, they will gather at the Victoria Park to join the
"Municipal Councils' Millennium Carnival" where they will
participate in a countdown ceremony to welcome the new Millennium
with the public. 
</P>
