<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bridge Inaugurated to Link Scandinavia, Denmark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Oresund Strait bridge,
which connects the Scandinavian Peninsula with Denmark, was
inaugurated Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 7.8-kilometer road and rail bridge also completes the link
between Scandinavia and the European Continent. Denmark already
has links with the mainland through the Great Belt bridge and the
Kleiner Belt bridge.
</P>
<P>
After the last 140-meter-long concrete section was put in place
on Saturday morning, Crown Princess Victoria of Sweden, Crown
Prince Frederik of Denmark, and another 700 honored guests
attended the inauguration ceremony on the double-decked bridge 68
meters above the sea.
</P>
<P>
Danish Trade Minister Pia Gjellerup and other officials
delivered speeches on the economic significance of the bridge to
Sweden and Denmark.
</P>
<P>
The Oresund Strait bridge has a four-lane motorway and a dual-
track electrified railway running from Malmo, the third largest
city of Sweden, to Denmark's Pepparholmen Island, a 4-kilometer-
long artificial island which in turn has a 4-kilometer tunnel link
with the Danish capital Copenhagen. The construction of the tunnel
finished earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the 16-kilometer link between Denmark and
Sweden, comprising the Oresund Strait bridge, the Pepparholmen
Island and the tunnel, began in 1995. When it opens for traffic on
July 1, 2000, it will take just 10-12 minutes to travel between
the Danish capital and Malmo in Sweden, compared with today's 45-
minute ferry ride. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
