<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Falun Gong Practitioners Repent Folly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Former Falun Gong's
practitioners Chinawide are repenting their foolishness in
believing Falun Gong and are revealing its harmfulness with their
own sad stories.
</P>
<P>
Guo Shenghua, a lecturer and a Communist Party member from the
Shanghai Teachers' University, vowed to sever his ties with the
Falun Gong cult.
</P>
<P>
He said four year ago he started to practice Falun Gong out of
interest, and was soon addicted to it. After that, he neglected
his research work and alienated his friends.
</P>
<P>
He attributed his folly to insufficient study of Marxist theory
and lack of political judgment.
</P>
<P>
Xu Yilian, another practitioner, living in south China's Hunan
province, has just been discharged from a local mental hospital.
He was the hospital's 15th patient afflicted with mental illness
after practicing Falun Gong.
</P>
<P>
These people trusted Li Hongzhi's "prophecy" that the world is
about to blow up, and his promise that one can become immortal if
he or she practices Falun Gong. Such people often suffer from
severe fever and mental instability, according to doctors.
</P>
<P>
Local hospitals have organized a special group to give these
people immediate treatment, and many have become normal and
realized Falun Gong's mischief.
</P>
<P>
Three daughters of a Falun Gong victim in east China's Anhui
province told reporters, in tears, that Falun Gong killed their
parents.
</P>
<P>
"After practicing Falun Gong, my mother refused to take
medicine or receive any kind of medical treatment. We saw her high
blood pressure and heart disease getting worse day by day," one
daughter said.
</P>
<P>
"We forced her to go to a hospital, which made her better for
some time, but she turned to the witchcraft again, and killed
herself in the end," she said.
</P>
<P>
His father was extremely upset afterwards, and died of cerebral
bleeding just two weeks after their mother's death.
</P>
<P>
To save more people from Falun Gong, local authorities and
departments Chinawide have made various efforts. In Shenyang, an
industrial base in north China, former practitioners of the Anshan
Iron and Steel Company have attentively studied the local
government's publicity brochures on getting rid of superstitious
ideas and fostering scientific thought.  
</P>
</TEXT>
