<HEADLINE> Pak Fully Capable of Thwarting Any Aggression: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minster Nawaz
Sharif Saturday said that his country is fully capable of giving
telling response to enemy if war was thrust on it.
</P>
<P>
"There should not be any doubt in this respect," he said in his
address at the national ceremony here to mark the country's 52nd
independence day.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said the Kargil incident has drawn the attention of the
international community and all major powers towards the Kashmir
issue and that "they have been compelled to realize that peace
cannot be established in the sub-continent until an urgent
solution of Kashmir issue."
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan cannot remain a silent spectator over the
"inhuman and barbaric atrocities" being committed by Indian
security forces in the southern part of Kashmir controlled by
them.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sharif said Pakistan has always endeavored for a
peaceful settlement of the Kashmir issue.
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan had appealed to the Kashmiri Mujahideen
(freedom fighters) to withdraw from Kargil heights so that
"tension is reduced and atmosphere for talks can be restored."
</P>
<P>
However, Pakistan's restraint should never be construed as a
sign of weakness, he warned.
</P>
<P>
Sharif regretted that India had shot down a naval aircraft of
Pakistan under training on August 10 resulting in the death of 16
people on board.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said the entire world is now well aware of the fact that
Kashmir is a basic dispute. "Unless this problem is resolved
according to United Nations resolutions and wishes of the Kashmiri
people, there will be no peace in South Asia." 
</P>
</TEXT>
