<HEADLINE> Ugandan Firms to Exhibit at Rwanda Expo'99 Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Some 18 Ugandan companies are
preparing to participate in the Rwanda Expo'99 International Trade
Fair slated for August 21-29 in a bid to penetrate the regional
market.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's participation, being facilitated by the Uganda Export
Promotion Board, also serves as a launch pad for the country's
products in Burundi and the Democratic Republic of the Congo
(DRC), the New Vision reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This show is important to the Ugandan business community,
particularly the manufacturers, because the volume of bilateral
trade has increased significantly.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda is becoming the destination for Ugandan products. In
1998, Uganda exported goods worth 70.4 million U.S. dollars to
Rwanda compared to 46.1 million dollars to Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's exports to Rwanda include bicycles, dairy products,
edible oil, soap, beer, Uganda Waragi, plastics and roofing
materials. 
</P>
