<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Social Security Program to Cover Migrant Filipinos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Around 200,000 overseas Filipino
workers (OFWs) are expected to become members of the Social
Security System (SSS) in the months ahead following the government
efforts to open new SSS offices abroad and offer benefits to OFWs,
a report said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report, which was issued here by the SSS, said that it has
recently opened offices in various foreign capitals to provide
social security coverage to migrant Filipinos.
</P>
<P>
"We recognize the need of our countrymen abroad for social
security protection," said SSS President Carlos Arellano in the
report. "More offices will be opened as the need arises."
</P>
<P>
"By being active SSS members, OFWs and their beneficiaries are
eligible to claim benefits and avail of loan privileges. An
estimated 200,000 OFWs worldwide are expected to join the SSS as
voluntary members in the next several months," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, about 4 million OFWs are working
overseas. They remit over 5 billion U.S. dollars annually to their
country.
</P>
<P>
The SSS report said that SSS offices abroad will receive and
process applications for membership as well as claims for
benefits, including disability assistance, livelihood assistance
and repatriation aid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
