<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East Timor's Autonomy Ballot Campaign Starts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Two rival camps in East Timor
kicked off their campaigns ahead of the August 30
U.N.-administered autonomy ballot on Saturday, according to the
Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the 14-day campaign, Governor Abilio Jose Osorio
Soares is of the view that a door-to-door campaign model is much
better than others to implement in avoiding the two rival groups
from any unexpected possibilities.
</P>
<P>
"The door-to-door campaign model will give more security
guarantees than such other models as a massive gathering," he told
a press conference in Dili, capital of East Timor.
</P>
<P>
He said the civil servants who planned or wanted to be involved
in the campaign must leave out their official uniforms so that
their involvement in it is for a personal basis as part of East
Timorese society.
</P>
<P>
They cannot use any local government-owned facilities, like
funds and vehicles, in participating in the pro-autonomy campaign
rallies, he said, adding that the local administration will be
neutral during the campaign period.
</P>
<P>
Soares called on his people to realize the importance of a
conducive situation during the campaign period, in the balloting
day and after the ballot.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the U.N. Mission in East Timor (UNAMET) officials
to explain the autonomy package that the governments of Indonesia
and Portugal and U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan had approved in
the New York Agreement on May 5.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, senior officials of Indonesia, Portugal and the U.N.
endorsed the formation of a consultative body in East Timor to
facilitate peace and cooperation following the ballot on the
territory's future.
</P>
<P>
The body would be made up of 25 representatives, U.N. special
envoy Jamsheed Marker said after completing the two-day tripartite
talks at the Foreign Ministry here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The list of the members would be announced soon, he added.
</P>
<P>
Marker said the tripartite talks would reconvene in Lisbon on
August 26 "in order to continue the discussion on the remaining
stages of the process."
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Indonesian delegation Nugroho Wisnumurti, who
is director general for political affairs at the Foreign Ministry,
said the consultative body would begin its tasks on August 31.
</P>
<P>
Under a U.N.-brokered agreement with Portugal, Indonesia agreed
to hold the direct ballot on August 30. The ballot will allow the
territory's people to choose whether their homeland should become
an autonomous region within Indonesia or totally independent.
</P>
<P>
The former Portuguese colony of East Timor was integrated into
Indonesia in 1976 in a move never recognized by the U.N., which
still considers Portugal as the administering power of the
territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
