<P>
PARIS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Saturday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The merger of French banks has come into a chaos, as the
Banque Nationale de Paris will obtain about 60 percent of the
shares of the bank Paribas, while waiting for an arbitration of
the French Ministry of Finance on its take-over bid against
another private bank, the Societe Generale, from which it has
taken control of 42 percent of shares.
</P>
<P>
-- The U.S. Mid-West state of Kansas has decided to allow
public school teachers either teach the theory of creation of the
Bible or the Darwinist theory of evolution of species according to
their choice of conscience. The decision by the Kansas State Board
of Education made up a victory for the ultra-conservative charches
who reject Darwinism.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- A new battle on the origin of life was launched after the U.
S. state of Kansas has made the teaching of the theory of
evolution of species by Charles Darwin a commonplace option for
teachers of public schools. Leaving the door open to creationist
thesis and obscurantism, the decision has triggered a political
and scientific outcry in the United States.
</P>
<P>
-- Russian troops started a major offensive on Friday to
eliminate the Islamic fighters who controlled several villages in
Dagestan. Moscow also threatened to bomb Chechnya which had served
as a base for the Islamists. 
