<HEADLINE> 25 Pilgrims Killed in Indian Bus Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-five pilgrims were
killed and 15 others injured when a bus overturned and plunged
into a deep ditch last night in Sitamarhi, Bihar, local officials
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sitamarhi District Magistrate R.N. Prasad said that the
accident occurred when the driver of the bus lost control over the
vehicle while negotiating a sharp bend.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of 25 people were recovered from the bus Saturday
morning, he added. The injured were admitted to a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
According to PTI, the victims were on their way to Sultanganj
from Sitamarhi for collecting holy water of river Ganga to offer
prayers at the temple of Lord Shiva in Deoghar. 
