<HEADLINE> Indian President Urges Nation to Address Population Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Indian President K.R.
Narayanan Saturday urged the nation to stem the tide of population
explosion in the country.
</P>
<P>
In his address to the nation on the eve of Independence Day, he
said that the country's population is "increasing at an alarming
rate and it has been estimated that India's population would cross
the one billion mark on Independence Day."
</P>
<P>
"One third of our people still live below the poverty level,"
he continued. "Almost half of our adult population is illiterate
and more than half of our children are undernourished."
</P>
<P>
He said there was need to have political and social will to
stem the tide of population explosion "instead of frittering away
our energies in the pursuit of the politics of power and pelf."
</P>
<P>
The president also stressed that the magnitude of these
problems is so immense that if the country does not address them
as "our over-riding political, social and economic priorities, the
galloping population would overwhelm us in the future." 
</P>
</TEXT>
