<HEADLINE> Philippine President Orders Probe Into Manila Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada has ordered the National Bureau of Investigation (NBI) to
conduct an exhaustive probe into Friday's explosion at the NBI
headquarters in Manila, which killed seven people, a senior
official said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora said in an interview here
that Estrada issued the order when he met NBI Director Federico
Opinion Friday night in the presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
"When Director Opinion reported to the president Friday, he
(Estrada) told him to get to the bottom of this case," Zamora
said.
</P>
<P>
In a separate interview here Saturday, Opinion said he has
relayed the president's directive to his staff immediately.
</P>
<P>
"I instructed them to conduct an exhaustive investigation,
whether it was the result of an accidental incident or if it was
deliberate. I want the truth to come out," he said.
</P>
<P>
A pre-dawn explosion Friday rocked the NBI building in Manila,
killing seven persons and injuring 12 others.
</P>
<P>
The blast, which was centered in the NBI's Special
Investigation Division (SID) office, sparked a two-hour fire.
Several firearms and ammunition as well as office equipment and
documents were damaged by the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, NBI Director Opinion said the explosion could be
targeted at SID chief Ruel Lazala, who headed a team which had
conducted a big drug operation recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
