<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Political Affairs Panel Holds Meeting In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The 15th meeting of the
Political Affairs Panel under the Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR) Preparatory Committee opened today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting will continue the research into the
transition of the Macao municipal government organization.
</P>
<P>
In order to guarantee the Macao's smooth transition and
successful transfer of power, the Macao SAR will continue to study
the topics concerning the Macao municipal government organization,
in accordance with the Basic Law of the Macao SAR and the specific
situation in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The topics include the establishment of non-governmental urban
organizations in Macao, and the retaining of the existing laws and
systems of the original Macao municipal government organization
with the exception for those in contravention of the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The relevant topics discussed at the meeting will also be
submitted for deliberation and approval at the plenary meeting of
the Macao SAR Preparatory Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
