<HEADLINE> Johnson Retains IBF Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- American Mark Johnson of the
United States retained his International Boxing Federation junior
bantamweight title by unanimous decision over Mexican Jorge
Lacierva in Mashantucket, Connecticut on Friday night when the
fight went to scorecards after eight rounds due to an accidental
cut.
</P>
<P>
Referee Steve Smoger stopped the bout due to a cut near the
challenger's right eye early in the ninth round. Since the gash
was the result of an ealier accidental headbutt, the outcome was
determined by the judges' totals through eight rounds.
</P>
</TEXT>
