<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanese Army Officer Arrested on Spying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 14 (Xinhua) -- A Lebanese army officer assigned
to the country's House Speaker Nabih Berri's security team has
been arrested on suspicion of spying for Israel.
</P>
<P>
First Adjutant Hussein Ali Alayyan, also known as Abu Alayyan,
was arrested Monday night at his home near the country's southern
coastal city of Sidon while in radio contact with an unidentified
party, a security source said.
</P>
<P>
Alayyan was allegedly communicating with members of Israel's
Mossad intelligence agency, the Daily Star reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
His wireless transmission apparatus and his official handgun
were confiscated, the source said, adding the suspect served on
the security team assigned to Berri's home.
</P>
<P>
Before he joined the army several years ago, Alayyan was a
member of Berri-led Amal Movement and led the group's
anti-Israeli resistance operations in the eastern sector of the
Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Berri's office declined comment on the report when contacted
by the paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
