<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Three-time champion Brazil secured
the
final berth here Saturday when they topplled Holland 3-0 at the
one million U.S. dollars World Women's Volleyball Grand Prix Macao
Leg.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, who made an easy work of the Italians in straight sets
Friday, showed their superiority of sharp offence and stable
defence and led all the way to finish the match with scores of 25-
18, 25-20 and 25-18 in 65 minutes.
</P>
<P>
"For the final on Sunday, probaly against China, it's going to
be a tough match, we have to play better," said Brazilian head
coach Bernardo Rocha de Rezende.
</P>
<P>
"The reason we lost so easily is we are too tired because
yesterday's match against China was finished too late, and because
the brazilans played better than yesterday againt Italy," said
Dutch head coach Pierre Mathieu.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday Brazil is to meet the winner between China and Italy
later Saturday. 
</P>
