<HEADLINE> Malaysian Trade Mission to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 14 (Xinhua) -- A Malaysian trade and
investment mission will visit China from August 17 to 27 to boost
bilateral trade links and investments, it was announced here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The mission, to be led by Deputy International Trade and
Industry Minister Kerk Choo Ting, aims to inform the business
community in China of the trade and investment opportunities in
Malaysia, the Ministry of International Trade and Industry (MITI)
said in a statement here.
</P>
<P>
The mission will also seek investment opportunities in China in
sectors such as property development, food processing, medicinal
products and cosmetic products, it said.
</P>
<P>
The mission also hopes to promote joint venture investments in
Malaysia related to tourism, property and commercial development
sectors, business consultancy on information technology (IT) and
IT-related projects, and on-shore and off-shore structural
fabrication for the oil and gas industries.
</P>
<P>
The mission will seek export opportunities for Malaysian
products in China.
</P>
<P>
The mission will also update the business community in China on
Malaysia's current economic situation and the various measures
undertaken by the government to revitalize the economy.
</P>
<P>
The mission, which will comprise representatives from local
governments and 18 private sector members representing 15
companies, officials of the MITI, Malaysian External Trade
Development Corporation and Malaysian Industrial Development
Authority, will visit Beijing, Dalian and Shanghai, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
