<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Establish Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Work for the establishment of the
first Bangladeshi government-initiated industrial park is likely
to start by the end of this year, as primary preparatory work has
been completed to make it a reality in the country, the New Nation
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The government-sponsored industrial park will be established in
Sirajganj district, 128 km northwest of here, on the eastern side
of the Jamuna multipurpose bridge, Industry Ministry sources were
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Around 500 acres of land have been selected to establish the
park, they said, adding that the Board of Investment will develop
necessary facilities so that industrial units can get all sorts of
proper support.
</P>
<P>
Large, medium-sized and small industrial units will get
permission to establish their units in the park, which will be
known as the Sirajganj Industrial Park.
</P>
<P>
The government with its own initiative will develop the
infrastructure necessary to establish the park, in which the
industrial plots will be distributed and allotted to the
entrepreneurs in the private sector, they said.
</P>
<P>
The industrial park will mobilize all the modern facilities,
services support and infrastructural amenities to make the park
equal to global standards, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
