<HEADLINE> Thai Athletes Celebrate Victory in SEA Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The successful Thai athletes,
who have returned home from the 20th Southeast Asian (SEA) Games
in Brunei, were feted at a party Friday night to celebrate their
victory in the latest regional extravaganza.
</P>
<P>
The Thai athletics squad won 20 gold medals, 11 silvers and 13
bronze, which was conform with the plan for Thailand as king of
this sport.
</P>
<P>
According to Police General Pracha Promnok, president of the
Amateur Athletics Association of Thailand (AAAT), the association
will present the winners with 50,000 baht (1,350 U.S. dollars) for
a gold, 15,000 baht (405 dollars) for a silver and 10,000 baht (
270 dollars) for a bronze.
</P>
<P>
For the team gold, the AAAT will give each team 200,000 baht (5,
400 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Pracha said there were plans to send sprinter Reanchai
Seehawong, who won three golds, to an intensive training course in
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Reanchai won his golds in the 100 meters with 10.26 seconds,
200 meters with 20.69 seconds and 4x100 relay with 39.11 seconds.
He has automatically qualified for the Sydney Olympics next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
