<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Project Gets Support From Prosperous Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The world's largest hydro-
electric power project, which is being built at the Three Gorges
of the Yangtze River, is getting funding from the booming southern
Chinese province of Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
The project has used 230 million yuan (27.7 million US dollars)
in funds channeled through Guangdong Province for the dam,
relocation of local people, and for public facilities in the last
six years, according to a provincial government official.
</P>
<P>
Feng Keye, who is in charge of financial aid for the project,
in Guangdong, says that the province has had a big responsibility
in building energy, telecommunications, and transportation systems
in the new communities for the relocated people, in answer to the
central government's call for help.
</P>
<P>
Private firms in Guangdong have taken over a number of
lackluster businesses near the dam project site through mergers or
outright purchases to help them leave an area that will be under
water when the dam is completed in early next century. 
</P>
