<HEADLINE> Thai Exports Grow Slightly in January-July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports rose by a
mere 0.62 percent in value in the first 7 months of this year
while the imports grew 8.09 percent, state television reported on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Somchainuek Hengtrakul, director-general of the Customs
Department, was quoted as saying at a meeting on Friday that the
exports and imports during the period were valued at 31.8 billion
and 27.1 billion U.S. dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
But the Ministry of Commerce is still confident of achieving a
target of 4 percent growth this year if monthly exports can be
maintained at 4.8-4.9 billion dollars for the rest of the year,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister and Commerce Minister Supachai
Panitchpakdi was also quoted as saying at the meeting that the
maximum target of monthly exports was 5 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said Thailand should maintain standards of commodity goods
in terms of quality and shipment. If not, Thailand will lose
export markets to rivals because of tougher price competition in
world markets. 
</P>
