<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Crude Oil Price Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan crude basket
price rose to 17.28 U.S. dollars per barrel, the country's Mining
and Energy Ministry said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This level represented a 89 percent recovery in oil prices so
far this year.
</P>
<P>
The oil prices have recovered by more than six dollars since
March thanks to an output cut of two million barrels, a decision
made by the producing countries on March 12, which will hold until
April 2000.
</P>
<P>
The oil basket price dropped 5.69 dollars per barrel in 1998
and, as a result, the Venezuelan government lost six billion
dollars or 43.5 percent in its revenue.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the state oil company Petroleos de Venezuela saw its
profits down by 84 percent to 766 million dollars due to the oil
market crisis. 
</P>
