<HEADLINE> 3 Killed, 11 Injured in Fresh Clash in Ambon, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- At least three villagers of
Batumerah were killed and 11 others injured after being allegedly
shot by security forces in a fresh communal clash on Friday in
Ambon, capital of Indonesia's Maluku, Antara news agency reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"The number of victims may still rise since the clashes are
continuing," a family member of a victim was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the clash happened after Batumerah was
attacked by a number of people from Hatiwe Kecil.
</P>
<P>
He said most of the victims, both the dead and injured, were
hit by bullets fired by Maluku police Mobile Brigade members.
</P>
<P>
The fresh clash was a continuation of previous ones in Ambon,
when a number of houses and office buildings in Aster of Hatiwe
Kecil were burnt on Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Ambon and several other islands in Maluku province have been
the scene of violent clashes between Muslim and Christian groups
since mid-January.
</P>
<P>
Communal clashes that occurred during the period between July
27 and August 12 have already taken a toll of 104 lives, and 200
others were injured.
</P>
<P>
Most of Indonesia's 202 million people are Muslim. Maluku is a
pre-dominantly Christian province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
