<HEADLINE> U.S., Ecuador Stage Joint Naval Maneuvers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The United States and Ecuador are
carrying out the Unitas naval maneuvers off the coast of the South
American country from August 13 to 22.
</P>
<P>
The maneuvers include landing operations and theoretical-
practical instruction, said the Ecuadorian naval authorities.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Navy No. 30 Force contributes six ships -- a frigate,
a destroyer, a searching ship, a landing ship, a Coast Guard
cutter and a nuclear submarine, while Ecuador participates with a
submarine and four ships.
</P>
<P>
The maneuvers will be carried out along the coasts of Guayas
and Manabi provinces in the eastern Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Coast Guard team has a mission for Saturday to
coordinate the strategies with its Ecuadorian counterpart in the
Navy Coast Guard Commando dock, located in the Southern Naval Base.
</P>
<P>
Initiated in 1960 by U.S. Admiral Arleigh A. Burke, the Unitas
maneuvers are held jointly by the navies of the United States and
several Latin American countries. 
</P>
