power and transportation facilities destroyed in the 78-day NATO
bombing, increasing production and exports and accelerating
economic and social reforms.
</P>
<P>
Further liberalization of the foreign trade system and the
resumption of the talks aimed to bring Yugoslavia back to the
world economic and political process are critical for realizing
these economic goals, said Filipovic. 
