</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Former Russian prime ministers Sergei Stepashin and
Yevgeny Primakov have agreed "on the forms and plans for
cooperation and the coordination of their work," the Interfax news
agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
They reached this agreement during a three-hour one-on-one
meeting Thursday at Primakov's country home, Interfax said,
quoting sources close to Stepashin. (Russia-Former PMs-Cooperation)
</P>
<P>
