<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Pushing Research Institutions into Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province has been striving to make its scientific institutions
more market-orientated by turning scientific organizations
specializing in technological developments and consultancy into
corporate entities.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial plan concerning the implementation of
scientific and technological reform, financial allocations for the
province's 39 scientific organizations engaged in technological
development will be halted gradually over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
Financial allocations to another 18 organizations specializing
in technical consultancy will also be reduced by 70 percent in the
years ahead.
</P>
<P>
The money thus saved will be used to support major scientific
and technological research programs in the concerned organizations.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Province, which is in the forefront of China's reform
and opening-up drive, has 69 provincial-level scientific and
technological organizations.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the plan, workers at these scientific and
technological organizations will be encouraged to buy stakes in
their respective new corporate entities -- share-holding companies
with limited liability or joint-stock cooperative companies --
following the reform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
