<HEADLINE> Northeastern China Preparing To Celebrate New Century </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The 'Ice and Snow World of the
Songhua River' is the theme of a December 31 event to mark the new
millennium in the capital of China's northernmost province,
Heilongjiang.
</P>
<P>
Tourism department sources say that it is part of a series of
events to be held in 10 major Chinese cities to greet the 21st
century. Harbin will build a tourist center to be used for the
event at a cost of 30 million yuan (3.6 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The 280,000-sq.m. area will have more than 10,000 ice
sculptures, colored ice, warm water springs, and artificial snow
for the eight-week celebration. There will also be an ice art show
and a millennium tour.
</P>
<P>
The National Tourism Administration and China Central
Television will have live broadcasts of the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Harbin has held an ice and snow festival every year since 1985.
</P>
