<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vismara Wins Second Gold at Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Italy's European
championships runner-up Lorenzo Vismara on Friday won his second
gold medal at the Military World Games here when he took the men's
100 meters freestyle.
</P>
<P>
He clocked 49.56 seconds, ahead of silver medalist Sergei
Ashikhmin of Russia at 50.71. Another Russian Dmitry Chernychov
timed 51.37 to finish third.
</P>
<P>
Vismara set the International Military Sports Council record in
the event.
</P>
<P>
"I am very satisfied with the victory, especially for the fact
that I had prepared for the European Championship in Istanbul,"
said Vismara, also the winner in Thursday's 50 meters freestyle.
</P>
<P>
"I managed to stay in good shape and set the new CISM record,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
In women's 100 meters backstroke, Russia's Yuliya Fomenko beat
China's world record holder He Cihong to second place.
</P>
<P>
Fomenko timed one minute 3.74 seconds, nearly one full second
ahead of He, whose world record of 1:00.16 remains intact since
1994.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very happy about the gold medal," said Fomenko after the
win.
</P>
<P>
But another Chinese Le Ying swam well in women's 200 meters
freestyle to beat Fomenko to second place.
</P>
<P>
She clocked 2:02.31 to snatch the gold, followed by Fomenko in
second place and Zhang Dan of China in third.
</P>
<P>
"I was not in top form these days but winning a gold medal of
course made me happy," said Le. 
</P>
