<HEADLINE> China Pockets Five More Golds at Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China pocketed five more gold
medals at the Military World Games here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
China monopolized the men's competition in the military
pentathlon as they won both the individual and team titles.
</P>
<P>
Yang Chunyi won the individual gold and helped his team to take
the team event with a total of 21,663.9 points.
</P>
<P>
Brazil was second only 12.5 points behind to finish at 21,651.4.
</P>
<P>
"It was the second time in 11 years that I won an individual
title in a major competition," said Yang, who will retire after
the games.
</P>
<P>
"Today's victory gives me a good career ending," he added.
</P>
<P>
In swimming, Le Ying beat Russian Yuliya Fomenko to second
place to win the women's 200 meters freestyle.
</P>
<P>
She clocked two minutes 2.31 seconds, 1.21 seconds ahead
Fomenko.
</P>
<P>
In taekwondo, China's Asia Games runner-up He Luming won the
women's 67kg category.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jing took the women's one-meter board to complete the day
's gold digging for China. 
</P>
