<HEADLINE> Pistons Hire McHone, Drew Assistant Coaches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Detroit Pistons coach Alvin
Gentry today filled out his staff, hiring Mo McHone and Larry Drew
to join assistant George Irvine.
</P>
<P>
McHone just completed a coaching stint for USA Basketball,
leading a collection of CBA All-Stars to a silver medal at the Pan
Am Games. McHone led the Skeyforce to four CBA Finals appearances
in five years.
</P>
<P>
Drew served as an assistant coach the past seven seasons with
the Los Angeles Lakers, but new coach Phil Jackson opted to re-
unite with his former Chicago Bulls staff of Tex Winter, Jim
Cleamons and Johnnie Rodgers. Drew was an assistant for Laker
coaches Randy Pfund, Del Harris and Kurt Rambis.
</P>
<P>
McHone also has ectensive NBA experience, serving an assistant
to Stan Albeck with both the Cleveland Cavaliers and San Antonio
Spurs from 1979-83. McHone was named interim coach of the Spurs
during the 1984-85 season, posting an 11-20 mark.
</P>
<P>
Drew was originally drafted by the Pistons with the 17th
overall pick in the 1980 draft. After starting as an advance scout,
Drew has been spending more time on the sidelines in recent years,
including ocaching the Lakers in summer leagues. 
</P>
