<HEADLINE> Hill: I Have Justified My 5m Pay Packet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Formula one driver Damon Hill
admitted on Friday that he did not deliver on his whopping 5
million pounds-a-year pay packet.
</P>
<P>
The former world champion revealed the failings and
frustrations of his final season in Formula One which saw him
controversially quit the last race in Germany.
</P>
<P>
"I feel like I have gone from Roadrunner to Wile E. Coyote,"
said Hill, referring to the famous cartoon characters, after
crashing out of Friday's first practice for Sunday's Hungarian
Grand Prix. "Nothing I do seems to work." If Hill resembled the
Roadrunner, an unstoppable speed merchant, during his 1996
championship winning year, this season he has been more like the
hapless coyote who failed in everything he did.
</P>
<P>
"It has been very, very frustrating this season," added the
Jordan driver who came close to quitting last month but will
retire at the end of the campaign.
</P>
<P>
"I have not delivered and that makes it awkward when you know
you have not fufilled your potential.
</P>
<P>
"It has been tough to bear and I have shown that as I have lost
my temper a few times. But I wouldn't be a racing driver if I didn
't have that aggression.
</P>
<P>
"I feel like I am not in control of the car. If I could control
the car everything else would be alright.
</P>
<P>
"It has been quite a disappointing year, not only because I
have had a lot of bad luck but because when I have had
opportunities I have not done as well as I would have hoped.
</P>
<P>
"The car has obviously been a better car throughout the year
than last year, and that has made it more difficult for myself."
</P>
<P>
Hill, who will be 39 next month, has managed just five points
from 10 races this year compared to the 33 collected by Heinz-
Harald Frentzen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
