<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stock Prices Soar On Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose
sharply Friday as a government report on wholesale prices eased
concerns about higher interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 184.26 or 1.7
percent at 10,973.65. The blue chip index rose 1.59 points
Thursday,
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 29.52 or 2.18 percent at 1,327.68 and the
technology heavy Nasdaq index rose 88.32 or 3.83 percent at
2,637.81.
</P>
<P>
Stocks soared after the Labor Department reported that
wholesale prices rose a less-than-expected 0.2 percent in July,
rising hopes that the Federal Reserve would not take aggressive
actions to prevent inflation from the U.S. economy. The moderate
rises in wholesale prices suggested inflation remained under
control.
</P>
<P>
Investors have been worried about the possibility of raising
interest rates for the second time in the Summer after the
Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan warned three weeks ago
that the Federal Reserve would act "promptly and forcefully" to
preempt inflation if new data suggested that the pace of cost and
price increases will be picking up. Investors also fear a third
rate increase if risks rise in inflation.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 10.75 at 621.38 and the
American Stock Exchange index rose 3.09 at 783.74. The Russell
2000 index of smaller companies rose 5.23 at 434.05.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 2-to-1 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,951 up, 1,077 down and
516 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 689.97 million shares from 742.42
million in the previous session.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
